<HEADLINE> Blast in Chinese Coal Mine Kills 12  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEIJING (AP) -- Gas exploded in a coal mine in southwestern
China, killing 12 miners and injuring 13 others, officials said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The blast occurred Sunday morning in the Tianba Coal Mine in
Qujing, a city in Yunnan province, said a city official contacted
by telephone. The cause is under investigation, although officials
suspect the gas may have been ignited by dynamite used in blasting.
</P>
<P>
   China has the world's most dangerous coal mines, with thousands
of deaths a year and fatal explosions and fires almost weekly.
</P>
