<HEADLINE> Stocks Mixed in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are mixed in early trading, weighed
down by weakness in technology issues. The Dow Jones industrial
average is up two points in today's early going. Advancing issues
on the New York Stock Exchange hold a slim lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off more than 50 points and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index is down nearly two points.
</P>
<P>
   The stock futures headed lower about an hour before the opening
bell, when BMC Software announced an earnings shortfall. That,
along with a warning issued by Computer Associates and Centura
Banks is reminding investors that a slowing economy may put a
damper on earnings.
</P>
