<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Asks Fox To Visit D.C.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP)-- President Clinton said Wednesday Mexican
President-elect Vicente Fox is welcome to visit Washington at any
time.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton spoke a day after Fox said he intends to make a U.S.
visit soon to pursue his goal of having the two countries become
''true partners, true neighbors, and true friends.''
</P>
<P>
   In a congratulatory telephone call on Monday, Clinton said he
told Fox ''he would be welcome here at any time if he would come
up.''
</P>
<P>
   He told reporters it would be useful to get the relationship
started before Fox begins a six-year term on Dec. 1.
</P>
<P>
   ''Most of his term will unfold with the next president,''
Clinton noted. ''But the relationship that we have with Mexico
needs to go beyond individual personalities always, because we have
too much in common and too much of a future to build together.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
