<HEADLINE> Entertainment Highlights in History  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Entertainment highlights during the week of July
9-15:
<TEXT>
<P>
   65 years ago: Spencer Tracy and Jimmy Stewart starred in ''The
Murder Man.'' It was Stewart's first feature film role. He played a
reporter named Shorty.
</P>
<P>
   55 years ago: Burgess Meredith and Robert Mitchum starred in
''The Story of G.I. Joe.''
</P>
<P>
   50 years ago: ''Your Hit Parade'' premiered on NBC. The show
featured a cast of vocalists and dancers.
</P>
<P>
   45 yeas ago: ''Mister Roberts,'' starring Henry Fonda, James
Cagney, Jack Lemmon and William Powell, opened at Radio City Music
Hall in New York City.
</P>
<P>
   And Bill Haley's ''(We're Gonna) Rock Around the Clock'' was No.
1 on the U.S. singles chart.
</P>
<P>
   35 years ago: Elizabeth Taylor and Richard Burton starred in
''The Sandpiper.'' The soundtrack included the Oscar-winning ''The
Shadow of Your Smile.''
</P>
<P>
   30 years ago: Peter Boyle and Susan Sarandon starred in ''Joe.''
It was Sarandon's film debut.
</P>
<P>
   15 years ago: ''Live Aid'' concerts to help bring relief to
famine-ridden African nations were held in London, Philadelphia and
other cities. ''Live Aid'' was organized by singer Bob Geldof and
featured dozens of top entertainers.
</P>
<P>
   And Kevin Kline, Kevin Costner, Scott Glenn and Danny Glover
starred in ''Silverado.''
</P>
<P>
   10 years ago: Actress Esther Rolle became the first woman to
receive the NAACP Chairman's Civil Rights Leadership Award. She was
honored for her work in helping raise the image of blacks through
her stage, television and movie work.
</P>
<P>
   British rock star David Bowie stopped his concert to take up the
cause of the rap group 2 Live Crew and its right to produce and
perform its music. ''I've been listening to the album by 2 Live
Crew,'' he said after stopping in the middle of the song, ''Young
Americans.'' ''It's not the best album that's ever been made, but
when I heard they banned it, I went out and bought it.''
</P>
<P>
   Rock star Madonna's ''Blond Ambition'' tour arrived in Italy to
a less-than-sellout crowd after weeks of protests by Roman Catholic
organizations. The show had angered the church and pro-family
groups that objected to the lingerie-clad Madonna using a crucifix
and other Christian symbols during her sexually suggestive
performance.
</P>
<P>
   And Patrick Swayze, Demi Moore and Whoopi Goldberg starred in
''Ghost.''
</P>
<P>
   Spoken 15 years ago:
</P>
<P>
   ''My real hope is to be able to fly in a space shuttle one day.
I'm not going to write a song about space until I'm up there and
can write about the real thing.'' -- Singer John Denver.
</P>
<P>
   Spoken 10 years ago:
</P>
<P>
   ''I had to watch my death. I had to see myself in the coffin. I
had to be present for my funeral -- really sort of blew me out of
the water.'' -- Patrick Swayze, on his role in ''Ghost.''
</P>
</TEXT>
