<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Courtney Love is condemning music piracy, but she isn't
referring to music freely distributed over the Internet. ''It's not
piracy when kids swap music on the Internet,'' she says. The
outspoken singer-actress says record companies are the real pirates
because they pay artists so little for their work. Her stance
contrasts with that of other leading artists, who consider Napster
and other Internet music services a threat to royalty payments.
Love, a principal member of the band Hole, was born on July 9,
1964. Her film roles include ''Man on the Moon'' with Jim Carrey.
</P>
<P>
   Tom Hanks dropped 60 pounds for his role in the upcoming film
''Cast Away.'' Hanks, who was born on July 9, 1956, plays a Federal
Express executive who is stranded on a desert island for four
years. ''It's almost like making a silent movie,'' said Hanks,
whose previous films include ''Saving Private Ryan.'' ''You have to
tell every aspect of the story physically, being totally alone.''
The film is set for a Christmas release.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays July 9-15:
</P>
<P>
   July 9: Actor Brian Dennehy is 62. Actor Richard Roundtree is
58. Actor Chris Cooper is 49. R&AMP;B singer Debbie Sledge of Sister
Sledge is 46. Actor Jimmy Smits is 45. Actor Tom Hanks is 44.
Actress Kelly McGillis is 43. Singer Jim Kerr of Simple Minds is
41. Singer-actress Courtney Love is 36. Actor Scott Grimes (''Party
of Five'') is 29. Actor Fred Savage is 24.
</P>
<P>
   July 10: Folk singer Arlo Guthrie is 53. Singer Neil Tennant of
Pet Shop Boys is 46. Musician Peter DiStefano of Porno for Pyros is
35. Actor Thomas Ian Nicholas (''American Pie'') is 20. Singer
Jessica Simpson is 20.
</P>
