<HEADLINE> Tony Bennett Turns Wedding Singer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Tony Bennett turned wedding singer last weekend,
dropping by a ballroom reception with a smile and a song: ''I Left
my Heart in San Francisco,'' of course.
</P>
<P>
   The 73-year-old crooner had just finished a sold-out show in
Manchester, England, and was returning to his room at a posh hotel
when the bride's mother approached him for the favor.
</P>
<P>
   ''At first, we didn't think he was going to do it. Then, just
before he went to bed, he got up and sang,'' a Bennett spokeswoman
said in Wednesday's New York Post.
</P>
<P>
   Mom was almost in tears, the cuddling couple were amazed, and
the guests sang along with Bennett, she said.
</P>
