<HEADLINE> Defense Secretary To Visit China  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Defense Secretary William Cohen will travel to
China and Australia next week for talks on regional security
issues, including U.S. plans for developing a nationwide defense
against ballistic missiles.
</P>
<P>
   The Pentagon announced Wednesday that Cohen will leave Monday
for Beijing. It will be his first visit to China since January
1998. Plans for a return visit last year were canceled after the
mistaken U.S. bombing of the Chinese embassy in Belgrade,
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
   China strongly opposes the U.S. missile defense plan, contending
that it will trigger a renewed arms race.
</P>
<P>
   Cohen also will visit Shanghai before flying to Sydney for talks
with his Australian counterpart. He is to return to Washington on
July 17.
</P>
</TEXT>
