<HEADLINE> Police appeal for help in identifying body found in Atlantic County </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BUENA VISTA TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) - State Police are asking for
help identifying a corpse found Wednesday along a roadside in rural
Atlantic County.
</P>
<P>
   The body of a Hispanic man in his 30s was spotted by a passing
motorist on Jackson Road at about 10 a.m., State Police spokesman
John Hagerty said.
</P>
<P>
   The body, which was clad in a long-sleeved button-down shirt,
beige pants and a ''distinctive'' cowboy-insignia engraved brown
leather belt, was located about 20 yards from the road in a wooded
area. State Police believe it had been pulled from a car sometime
Tuesday night and dragged into underbrush.
</P>
<P>
   An autopsy was performed Wednesday, but results weren't released
immediately.
</P>
<P>
   ''The condition of the body indicated it was freshly dumped. And
there's no indication the individual died there,'' Hagerty said.
</P>
<P>
   The body is about 5-feet 5 inches tall and weighs 140 pounds.
</P>
<P>
   ''We figure the sooner we get out with a little bit of
information, the sooner we'll get something back,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
