<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Computer Associates International Inc., down $21.531 at $29.594
</P>
<P>
   The company said it expects to earn 26 cents to 31 cents a
share, below analysts' forecasts of 55 cents a share. Computer
Associates said several large deals were pushed back, the company's
mainframe business was weak and the European business
underperformed.
</P>
<P>
National Semiconductor, down $8.188 at $49.938
LSI Logic Corp., down $6.888 at $50.75
Micron Technology Inc., down $7.25 at $83
</P>
<P>
   Salomon Smith Barney downgraded the entire semiconductor sector,
warning that the industry may see a slowdown in shipments. The
semiconductor group has thrived in recent quarters.
</P>
<P>
Enesco Group Inc., up $1.75 at $6.75
</P>
<P>
   The company, which makes collectible figurines, has entered an
agreement to develop gift and collectible products based on Harry
Potter books. Enesco will develop an initial line of products for a
fall release, and another line in conjunction with the 2001 opening
of a film from Warner Bros. Pictures.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
