<DOCNO> APW20000705.0154 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 20:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Galarraga Leads Braves All-Stars  </HEADLINE>
By TOM SALADINO
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Andres Galarraga not only came back from a bout
with cancer, on Wednesday he made another huge stride, being
selected to the National League All-Star team.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta first baseman was among four Braves players added to
the squad, giving the Braves five players for Tuesday night's game
at Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   ''I feel very good, very excited,'' said Galarraga before
Wednesday night's game against the Montreal Expos.
</P>
<P>
   ''I want to say thank you to all the fans that gave me great
support last year and this year,'' he said. ''I thank God for
giving me my health and all the beautiful and happy things that
have happened to me this year. It's a gift.''
</P>
<P>
   Along with the Big Cat, who missed all of the 1999 season while
undergoing treatment for cancer, outfielder Andruw Jones and
pitchers Greg Maddux and Tom Glavine were picked to join third
baseman Chipper Jones, who was voted in by the fans.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know what else you can say about him,'' said Glavine.
''Everything he's done has been phenomenal. All we had hoped for
was to see him out on the field again, let alone on an All-Star
team. It's been a great story.''
</P>
<P>
   Bobby Cox of the Braves, the NL manager for the All-Star game,
</P>
<P>
   said there was never a doubt in picking Galarraga.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was second in the voting and he's got the numbers. He's
been our MVP the first half,'' Cox said.
</P>
<P>
   Galarraga was hitting .299 with 19 homers and 60 RBIs prior to
Wednesday night's game.
</P>
<P>
   ''It means a lot to me and my family to come back and play
baseball. Now to make the All-Star team is really something,''
Galarraga said.
</P>
<P>
   Mark McGwire of the Cardinals, elected to start at first, had
threatened not to play unless teammate and outfielder Jim Edmonds
was picked as a reserve.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire said Wednesday he was joking. Cox said he never heard
about McGwire's comments.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't read newspapers,'' Cox said. ''Edmonds had been on our
list for the last 3&AMP;frac12; weeks.''
</P>
<P>
   It will be the fifth All-Star appearance for Galarraga, the
first for Andruw Jones, the eighth for Maddux, the seventh for
Glavine and the fourth for Chipper Jones.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm just happy and my parents are happy,'' Andruw Jones said.
''It's my first All-Star game and I can't wait. It's something
special. You don't have to clean out your locker or pack a
suitcase. It's good to have it at home. That's doesn't happen very
often.''
</P>
<P>
   It's especially meaningful for Glavine, who has been with the
Braves' organization since the 1984 amateur draft.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's something I've wanted to be a part of since spring
training,'' he said, ''and is particularly special to me since I've
spent my whole career here.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
