<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 20:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yanks' Posada Makes All-Star Team  </HEADLINE>
By JOSH DUBOW
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Yankees manager Joe Torre knew he'd be taking
Jorge Posada to Atlanta with him for the All-Star game. He just
made Posada wait to find out the news.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm more than excited,'' the catcher said Wednesday after
finding out he was going to his first All-Star game. ''I couldn't
sleep last night to tell you the truth.''
</P>
<P>
   Posada's anxiousness was heightened when Torre told him Tuesday
that he needed to meet with his starting catcher before batting
practice Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   That's when Torre told Posada, Derek Jeter and Mariano Rivera
that they would join starter Bernie Williams for next Tuesday's
game in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've known in my mind for a long time that he is an
All-Star,'' said Torre, who will manage the AL team. ''It just
depended on how many other catchers were having All-Star years.''
</P>
<P>
   Posada (.314, 14 HRs, 49 RBIs entering Wednesday) beat out
Baltimore's Charles Johnson (.313, 19, 44) for the spot backing up
Texas' Ivan Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
   ''As long as the numbers are close, I don't think anybody has a
problem with it,'' Torre said. ''If my guy is hitting .260 and the
other guy is at .330, then I'm not going to take my guy. As long as
my guy's numbers are in the ballpark, every manager would do the
same thing.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson held no ill will toward Torre for picking his own
player.
</P>
<P>
   ''That's the way it should be,'' Johnson said. ''If he feels
that Posada is having a good year, he should bring his own guy to
the game. Good for him.''
</P>
<P>
   After getting the news, Posada immediately called his parents in
Puerto Rico and his wife. He had been planning to return to Puerto
Rico for the three-day break but instead will bring his parents to
Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   ''Every day my parents have been calling, 'Did they tell you
already? Did they tell you already?''' Posada said. ''They wanted
to come if I made it.''
</P>
<P>
   The All-Star selection was especially rewarding for Posada, who
struggled last year (.245, 12, 57) and was under pressure this
season as Joe Girardi's replacement.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm proud of him because of what he went through,'' said
Jeter, Posada's closest friend on the team. ''People doubted him.
He had the opportunity this year and made the most of it.''
</P>
<P>
   Girardi, now with the Chicago Cubs, also was pleased for his
former understudy.
</P>
<P>
   ''He deserves it,'' Girardi said. ''That's the reason I'm not
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Jeter, picked for his third All-Star team, said he still gets
excited about making the team.
</P>
<P>
   ''Every player wants to play in the All-Star game,'' Jeter said.
''If they say they don't, they're lying to you.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
