<HEADLINE> Braves Sign Pitcher Kamieniecki  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- The Braves signed right-hander Scott Kamieniecki
on Wednesday in an effort to bolster their injury-riddled pitching
staff.
</P>
<P>
   Kamieniecki, designated for assignment by the Cleveland Indians
on June 23, refused the assignment and became a free agent. He will
be available to pitch Thursday, when the Braves will have to make a
roster move.
</P>
<P>
   Kamieniecki was 1-3 with a 5.67 ERA in 26 games with the
Indians. He gave up 42 hits and 22 earned runs in 33 1-3 innings.
</P>
<P>
   After pitching for the the New York Yankees and Baltimore
Orioles, Kamieniecki was signed as a free agent by Cleveland in
December. He has a 51-58 career record.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta has seven pitchers on the disabled list, including John
Smoltz, Odalis Perez, David Cortes and Rudy Seanez, all out for the
season; and Greg McMichael, Luis Rivera and Kevin McGlinchy.
</P>
<P>
   Rivera is on a rehabilitation assignment in the minors and
McGlinchy will begin rehab Thursday at Triple-A Richmond.
</P>
