<HEADLINE> Three White Sox Selected All-Stars  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- While three White Sox were picked for
the All-Star game, Frank Thomas and Keith Foulke were left off the
American League roster.
</P>
<P>
   ''I am a little disappointed, because I deserved to be there,''
Thomas said. ''This is probably the best first half I've ever
had.''
</P>
<P>
   Thomas, an All-Star from 1993-97, entered Wednesday's game
against Kansas City with a .340 average, 25 homers and 72 RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   Foulke began the night with 16 saves.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've done too much in this league on a consistent basis to be
looked over,'' Thomas said.
</P>
<P>
   Picked from Chicago, which has the best record in baseball, were
outfielder Magglio Ordonez, second baseman Ray Durham and pitcher
James Baldwin.
</P>
<P>
   ''I feel for Frank because of the half he's had,'' White Sox
manager Jerry Manuel said. ''He's basically been carrying a young
team. He should have been a guy to go.''
</P>
<P>
   Ordonez and Durham are making their second All-Star appearances.
Baldwin is making his first.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's nice to be selected,'' Baldwin said. ''A lot of our guys
deserved to go. They've got to take a select few. I will definitely
dedicate this to my teammates. Without them, if it weren't for
them, I definitely wouldn't be in the situation I'm in.''
</P>
<P>
   Baldwin is 11-3 with a 3.79 ERA, while began the night 10th in
the AL in batting at .339 average. He has 19 home runs with 72
RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   Durham is hitting .284 with 13 home runs and 47 RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is a special ballclub,'' Thomas said. ''We're playing
great. Nothing can take anything away from this season. I'll just
deal with it.''
</P>
