<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sting 76, Sol 70  </HEADLINE>
By JENNA FRYER
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Rhonda Mapp scored 20 points -- including
the 1,000th point of her career -- as the Charlotte Sting won their
first home game of the season Wednesday night, 76-70 over the Miami
Sol.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte (3-13) lost a WNBA-record nine straight home games
before the victory. The Sting, who have lost 18 of their last 21
regular-season games, snapped a five-game overall losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Mapp, who scored her milestone points on her first basket of the
game, hit two free throws with 22 seconds to play to seal the
victory, and also had a game-high nine rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Miami (5-11), an expansion team, lost despite getting a career-
high 26 points from Sheri Sam.
</P>
<P>
   Sam hit a 3-pointer to tie it at 68 with 4:34 to play. But
Andrea Stinson and Shalonda Enis hit consecutive jumpers to put
Charlotte up 72-68 with 2:50 to play.
</P>
<P>
   Debbie Black hit two free throws to cut it to 72-70. After
turnovers by both teams, the Sol missed a chance to take the lead
when Black's 3-point attempt fell short with 34 seconds to go. Mapp
got the rebound and was fouled by Black. She hit both free throws
to give the Sting a 74-70 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Sam then missed a 3-pointer, Stinson got the rebound and was
fouled and hit both her free throws to seal the win.
</P>
<P>
   Enis finished with 16 points and Stinson scored 13.
</P>
<P>
   Katrina Colleton had 14 points for Miami and Marlies Askamp
scored all 12 of her points in the second half.
</P>
</TEXT>
