<HEADLINE> MetroStars 2, Burn 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Billy Walsh scored in the 59th
minute as the New York-New Jersey MetroStars beat Dallas 2-1 on
Wednesday night to extend their unbeaten streak to six games.
</P>
<P>
   Walsh's long shot deflected off Dallas midfielder Lazo Alavanja
before rolling past goalkeeper Matt Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas' Ted Eck opened the scoring in the 24th minute, ending
MetroStars goalkeeer Tim Howard's shutout streak at 203 minutes.
Clint Mathis tied it with a long shot in the 31st minute.
</P>
<P>
   The Eastern Division-leading MetroStars improved to 10-7-2,
while the Burn dropped to 7-11-3 overall and 0-9-2 on the road.
</P>
<P>
   MetroStars midfielder Tab Ramos learned before the game he had
been selected to rejoin the U.S. national team for its first two
World Cup qualifiers, on July 16 and 23. Ramos, plagued by
injuries, has not played for the United States since the 1998 World
Cup.
</P>
</TEXT>
