<HEADLINE> Storm 67, Lynx 60  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Robin Threatt scored a season-high 24 points
as the Seattle Storm ended a nine-game losing streak by beating the
Minnesota Lynx 67-60 Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The expansion Storm (3-13) held the Lynx to 39.3 percent
shooting from the field and their second-lowest point total of the
season.
</P>
<P>
   Threatt, who scored 22 points in a 81-60 loss to Utah on
Saturday, scored six points in a 12-0 run early in the second half
that put Seattle in control.
</P>
<P>
   The Lynx (10-6), who had won four of five and were unbeaten
against expansion teams, trailed by as many as 17 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Lynx defeated the Storm 65-53 last week, Seattle's worst
loss during its nine-game skid.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle led by only 30-29 at the break, but held Minnesota to
just two baskets in the first 12:11 of the second half.
</P>
<P>
   Kristin Folkl and Keitha Dickerson led Minnesota with 15 points
apiece.
</P>
<P>
   Charisse Sampson added 11 points for Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle jumped to a 9-0 lead in the first two minutes and never
trailed in the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota forward Katie Smith, who entered the game leading the
WNBA in scoring average at 22.5, was held to five points.
</P>
