<HEADLINE> Thunder 7, Ravens 6  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - Aaron Capista's two-run double in the
bottom of 12th lead the Trenton Thunder past the New Haven Ravens
7-6 Wednesday night in an Eastern League game.
</P>
<P>
   Capista's game-winning hit came after the Ravens had gone ahead
by one in the top of the inning on a home run by Juan Thomas.
</P>
<P>
   Reliever Joel Bennett (1-0) got the win for the Thunder despite
allowing the home run by Thomas. Justin Kaye (0-1) took the loss
for Ravens after surrendering the two Thunder runs in the 12th.
</P>
<P>
   The game was tied 5-5 after nine innings. The Ravens scored five
in the seventh, including a three-run homer by Blake Barthol. The
Thunder tied the game in the bottom of the inning on a two-run
double by Virgil Chevalier.
</P>
</TEXT>
